#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:33(title) 
msgid "Introduction to Desktop Customization"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:35(para) 
msgid "The great thing about KDE is the ability to customize just about every aspect of the desktop environment. Wallpapers, themes, widgets, color schemes, splash screens and more, the options for customization are endless."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:41(para) 
msgid "<ulink url=\"http://www.kde-look.org\">KDE-Look.org</ulink> is the number one location to find customized settings for your KDE desktop. Some of the applications within KDE even allow you to connect directly to KDE-Look and download a new configuration or image."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:48(para) 
msgid "For more detailed information on some of the customization options available to you, please refer to the <ulink type=\"help\" url=\"help:/khelpcenter/userguide/customizing-desktop.html\">Customizing and Appearance</ulink> section of the KDE Users' Manual."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:59(title) 
msgid "Desktop Tips"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:61(para) 
msgid "This section details some tips for using and customizing the desktop."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:66(title) 
msgid "Run programs automatically when KDE starts"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:70(para) 
msgid "The easiest way to run programs automatically when KDE starts is to use the <emphasis>Session Management</emphasis> feature of KDE. You can setup KDE exactly the way you'd like it to start every time you login."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:78(para) 
msgid "Choose <menuchoice><guimenu>K-Menu</guimenu><guisubmenu>System Settings</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Session Manager</guimenuitem></menuchoice> from the Advanced tab on the top and then under <emphasis>Advanced User Settings</emphasis> section. Click the <guibutton>Session Manager</guibutton> button on the right. Ensure that the <guibutton>Restore manually saved session</guibutton> checkbox is enabled."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:89(para) 
msgid "Launch all the applications you want running <emphasis>everytime you log in</emphasis>. Once you have everything set to your satisfaction, click choose <menuchoice><guimenu>K-Menu</guimenu><guisubmenu>Save Session</guisubmenu></menuchoice>. Every time you start KDE, you will return to this configuration."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:99(para) 
msgid "Another method to do this is to copy the desktop entry of the application you want to autostart from <filename>/usr/share/applications</filename> to the <filename>~/.kde/Autostart</filename> directory."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:109(title) 
msgid "Login automatically to KDE when the computer starts"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:111(para) 
msgid "It is possible to login a user automatically when the computer boots. This is not recommended for most computers, as it is not secure and may allow other users access to your information."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:119(para) 
msgid "Go to <application>System Settings</application> by going to <menuchoice><guimenu>KMenu</guimenu><guimenuitem>System Settings</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Under the <guilabel>Advanced</guilabel> tab select the <guilabel>Login Manager</guilabel>."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:127(para) 
msgid "Click on the <guibutton>Administrator Mode...</guibutton> and enter your user password to gain administrator privileges."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:134(para) 
msgid "Select the <guibutton>Convenience</guibutton> tab. Check the <guilabel>Enable Autologin</guilabel> and select the user to autologin from the drop down menu and select an appropriate time delay."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:144(title) 
msgid "Restart KDE without rebooting the computer"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:148(para) 
msgid "Save and close all open applications."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:154(para) 
msgid "Press <keycombo><keycap>Ctrl</keycap><keycap>Alt</keycap><keycap>Backspace</keycap></keycombo> to restart KDE or X-Windows."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:160(para) 
msgid "If <keycombo><keycap>Ctrl</keycap><keycap>Alt</keycap><keycap>Backspace</keycap></keycombo> is disabled, open <application>Konsole</application> by going to <menuchoice><guimenu>KMenu</guimenu><guisubmenu>System</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Konsole - Terminal Program</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. At the command prompt type the following and press the <keycap>Enter</keycap> key (if asked for a password, type in your user password followed by the <keycap>Enter</keycap> key): <screen>\nsudo /etc/init.d/kdm restart\n</screen>"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:168(para) 
msgid "(See <xref linkend=\"disable-ctrlaltbkspc\"/> to disable <keycombo><keycap>Ctrl</keycap><keycap>Alt</keycap><keycap>Backspace</keycap></keycombo>.)"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:176(title) 
msgid "Preventing the Ctrl-Alt-Backspace shortcut keys from restarting X"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:180(para) 
msgid "Make a backup copy of your existing <filename>/etc/X11/xorg.conf</filename> file. To do so, open <application>Konsole</application> by going to <menuchoice><guimenu>KMenu</guimenu><guisubmenu>System</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Konsole - Terminal Program</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. At the command prompt type the following and then press the <keycap>Enter</keycap> key (if asked for a password, type in your user password followed by the <keycap>Enter</keycap> key): <screen>\nsudo cp /etc/X11/xorg.conf /etc/X11/xorg.conf_backup\n</screen>"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:193(para) 
msgid "Open <filename>/etc/X11/xorg.conf</filename> for editing. To do so, press <keycombo><keycap>Alt</keycap><keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo> and at the <guilabel>Run Command</guilabel> dialog type the following and then press the <guibutton>OK</guibutton> key (if asked for a password, type in your user password followed by pressing the <guibutton>OK</guibutton> button): <screen>\nkdesu kwrite /etc/X11/xorg.conf\n</screen>"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:208(programlisting) 
#, no-wrap
msgid "\nSection\t\"ServerFlags\"\n\tOption\t\"DontZap\"\t\"yes\"\nEndSection\n"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:206(para) 
msgid "Add the following lines to the end of the file: <placeholder-1/>"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:217(para) 
msgid "Save the edited file and close out of <application>KWrite</application>."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:223(para) 
msgid "The change will take effect the next time you log in to KDE. If you want the change to take effect immediately, restart KDE manually. (See <xref linkend=\"restartwithoutreboot\"/>.)"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:232(title) 
msgid "Start a Program Manually"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:234(para) 
msgid "Sometimes it can be useful to start a program manually, for example when the program does not have an entry in the menu. This is easy to do with the <guilabel>Run Command</guilabel> dialog."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:242(para) 
msgid "Open the <guilabel>Run Command</guilabel> dialog by pressing <keycombo><keycap>Alt</keycap><keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo>"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:249(para) 
msgid "Enter the name of the program you wish to run, and press the <guibutton>OK</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:258(title) 
msgid "Automatically turn on NumLock when KDE starts"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:262(para) 
msgid "Open <application>System Settings</application> by going to <menuchoice><guimenu>KMenu</guimenu><guimenuitem>System Settings</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. In the <application>System Settings</application> window select the <guilabel>Keyboard &amp; Mouse</guilabel> option."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:270(para) 
msgid "Under the <guilabel>Keyboard</guilabel> section, locate the subsection titled <guilabel>NumLock on KDE Startup</guilabel>, enable the <guibutton>Turn On</guibutton> checkbox. Click on <guibutton>Apply</guibutton> to save your settings."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:279(para) 
msgid "The change will take effect the next time you log in to KDE. If you want to test it right away, turn off NumLock and restart KDE (see <xref linkend=\"restartwithoutreboot\"/>)."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:287(title) 
msgid "Handle help:/ links in Firefox like Konqueror"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:289(para) 
msgid "<application>Firefox</application> is not installed by default so in order for this to work you will have had to previously installed <application>Firefox</application>. Please refer to the <ulink type=\"help\" url=\"help:/kubuntu/add-applications/\">Adding Applications</ulink> documentation for more information on installing applications."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:297(para) 
msgid "<application>Konqueror</application> is able to handle help:/ <acronym>URL</acronym>s by default. <application>Firefox</application> is also able to handle these the same way however it requires you to manually edit the configuration of <application>Firefox</application> to do so. The following procedure will aide you in such configuration."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:307(para) 
msgid "Start <application>Firefox</application> by choosing left <menuchoice><guimenu>KMenu</guimenu><guisubmenu>Internet</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Firefox Web Browser</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:313(para) 
msgid "In the address bar type <userinput>about:config</userinput> and press the <keycap>Enter</keycap> key."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:320(para) 
msgid "<mousebutton>Right</mousebutton> click on the list and select <menuchoice><guimenu>New</guimenu><guimenuitem>Boolean</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Type <userinput>network.protocol-handler.external.help</userinput> as the <guilabel>Preference Name</guilabel> and <userinput>true</userinput> as the <guilabel>Value</guilabel>. Press the <guibutton>OK</guibutton> button when complete."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:331(para) 
msgid "<mousebutton>Right</mousebutton> click again on the list and select <menuchoice><guimenu>New</guimenu><guimenuitem>String</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. Type <userinput>network.protocol-handler.app.help</userinput> as the <guilabel>Preference Name</guilabel> and <userinput>khelpcenter</userinput> as the <guilabel>Value</guilabel>. Press the <guibutton>OK</guibutton> button when complete."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:344(title) 
msgid "Edit K-Menu"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:346(para) 
msgid "Kubuntu comes with the <application>KDE Menu Editor</application>, so you can customize your menus and add entries for applications that don't automatically appear after they are installed. To add, remove, or modify an entry, refer to the following procedure."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:355(para) 
msgid "Open <application>KDE Menu Editor</application> by <mousebutton>right</mousebutton> clicking on <application>KMenu</application> and choosing <guimenuitem>Menu Editor</guimenuitem>. If you have locked your <application>Kicker</application>, you can also open <application>KDE Menu Editor</application> by pressing <keycombo><keycap>Alt</keycap><keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo> and typing <userinput>kmenuedit</userinput> followed by pressing the <guibutton>OK</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:368(para) 
msgid "In <application>KDE Menu Editor</application>'s left-hand pane, choose the submenu the new entry should appear in."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:375(para) 
msgid "Choose <menuchoice><guimenu>File</guimenu><guimenuitem>New Item</guimenuitem></menuchoice> or press the <guibutton>New Item</guibutton> button. In the <guilabel>New Item</guilabel> window, choose a <guilabel>Name</guilabel>. Then add the <guilabel>Description</guilabel>, <guilabel>Comment</guilabel>, and <guilabel>Command</guilabel>. Select the icon by clicking on <guilabel>Icon</guilabel>. The <guilabel>Command</guilabel> will usually be the package name, <guilabel>Name</guilabel> is what will appear on the menu, and the <guilabel>Comment</guilabel> will appear in the tooltip that appears near the menu entry. <guilabel>Icons</guilabel> are chosen from <filename>/usr/share/icons/icon_theme</filename> directory by default, or can be chosen from anywhere in your files."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:390(para) 
msgid "To change the order of menu entries, click and drag the entry in the <application>KDE Menu Editor</application> window."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:397(title) 
msgid "Advanced Desktop Applets"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:399(para) 
msgid "<application>SuperKaramba</application> is a system for bringing mini programs (desklets) such as weather forecasts, news tickers, system information displays, or music player controls onto your desktop, where they are sitting there in a symbiotic relationship of eye candy and usefulness."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:408(para) 
msgid "Install the <application>superkaramba</application> package. For more information on installing extra applications, please refer to the <ulink type=\"help\" url=\"help:/kubuntu/add-applications/\">Adding Applications</ulink> documentation."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:416(para) 
msgid "Once installed, open <application>SuperKaramba</application> by going to <menuchoice><guimenu>KMenu</guimenu><guisubmenu>Utilities</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>SuperKaramba</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:423(para) 
msgid "To download extra applets for <application>SuperKaramba</application> you can either select the <guibutton>New Stuff...</guibutton> button in the main window or you can go to <ulink url=\"http://www.kde-look.org\">KDE-Look.org</ulink> and select the <emphasis>Karamba</emphasis> link."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:432(title) 
msgid "Install Extra Fonts"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:434(para) 
msgid "This section describes how to install extra fonts from the Kubuntu archives."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:441(para) 
msgid "For <emphasis role=\"bold\">international fonts</emphasis>, install the following packages (please refer to the <ulink type=\"help\" url=\"help:/kubuntu/add-applications/\">Adding Applications</ulink> documentation for help on installing extra applications):"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:449(literallayout) 
#, no-wrap
msgid "\nxfonts-intl-arabic\nxfonts-intl-asian\nxfonts-intl-chinese\nxfonts-intl-chinese-big\nxfonts-intl-european\nxfonts-intl-japanese \nxfonts-intl-japanese-big\nxfonts-intl-phonetic\n"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:463(para) 
msgid "For <emphasis role=\"bold\">Microsoft TrueType core fonts</emphasis>, install the <application>msttcorefonts</application> package (please refer to the <ulink type=\"help\" url=\"help:/kubuntu/add-applications/\">Adding Applications</ulink> documentation for help on installing extra applications)."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:473(para) 
msgid "For <emphasis role=\"bold\">Ghostscript fonts</emphasis>, install the <application>gsfonts-x11</application> package (please refer to the <ulink type=\"help\" url=\"help:/kubuntu/add-applications/\">Adding Applications</ulink> documentation for help on installing extra applications)."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:482(para) 
msgid "If you prefer to download individual fonts by hand, you can install them easily by opening <application>Konqueror</application> and typing <userinput>fonts:/</userinput> into the location bar. Then you can install the font, either system-wide or for personal use by dragging and dropping into the respective folders."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:493(title) 
msgid "Install Compiz Fusion"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:495(para) 
msgid "Compiz Fusion is a project that uses 3D graphics acceleration to bring new graphical effects and features to your desktop. The project resulted from the mergence of Compiz and Beryl (a previous project based on Compiz). This section describes how to install Compiz Fusion on Gutsy Gibbon."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:503(para) 
msgid "Before installing Compiz Fusion, you may need to check whether you have the correct drivers installed for your graphics card. Please refer to <ulink type=\"http\" url=\"http://www.compiz.org/NVidia\"/>, <ulink type=\"http\" url=\"http://www.compiz.org/ATI\"/> and <ulink type=\"http\" url=\"http://www.compiz.org/Intel\"/> for information about nVidia, ATI and Intel graphics card drivers respectively."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:515(para) 
msgid "Go to <menuchoice><guimenu>KMenu</guimenu><guisubmenu>System</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>Adept Manager - Manage Packages</guimenuitem></menuchoice> (when prompted for a password at the <guilabel>Run as root - KDE su</guilabel> dialog, type in your password and press the <guibutton>OK</guibutton> button)."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:523(para) 
msgid "Install the following packages: <literallayout>\ncompiz-kde\ncompiz-fusion-plugins-main\ncompiz-fusion-plugins-extra\ncompiz-config-settings-manager\n</literallayout>"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:535(para) 
msgid "After the installation finishes, you can run Compiz Fusion by pressing <keycombo><keycap>Alt</keycap><keycap>F2</keycap></keycombo> and typing the following at the <guilabel>Run Command</guilabel> dialog followed by pressing the <guibutton>OK</guibutton> button: <screen>\ncompiz --replace\n</screen>"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:547(para) 
msgid "The following procedure describes how to configure Compiz Fusion to run at start-up."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:554(para) 
msgid "Go to <filename>~/.kde/Autostart</filename> using <application>Konqueror</application>."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:561(para) 
msgid "Right click the content area and choose <menuchoice><guimenu>Create New</guimenu><guimenuitem>Link to Application</guimenuitem></menuchoice>. This opens a properties tabbed window."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:569(para) 
msgid "In the <guilabel>General</guilabel> tab, provide a descriptive name for the program e.g. Compiz-Fusion."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:576(para) 
msgid "Click the <guilabel>Application</guilabel> tab and type the following at the <guilabel>Command</guilabel> text box followed by pressing the <guibutton>OK</guibutton> button to finish and close the tabbed window: <screen>\ncompiz --replace\n</screen>"
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:585(para) 
msgid "From now on, when you start <application>KDE</application>, Compiz Fusion should start up automatically."
msgstr ""

#: config-desktop/C/config-desktop.xml:593(para) 
msgid "To configure Compiz Fusion, go to <menuchoice><guimenu>K-Menu</guimenu><guisubmenu>Settings</guisubmenu><guimenuitem>CompizConfig Settings Manager</guimenuitem></menuchoice>."
msgstr ""

